OR2019 <- Roughy1 %>% 
  filter(year == 2019)

  dplyr::group_by(Ground,Shot,Date, 'Shot Weight (kg)' = ShotWeight_kg,sex) %>%

  group_by(Ground, sex) %>% 
  add_tally() %>%

Data presented as proporation of number of females (F) and males (M) relative to the total catch within each spawning ground. OR2019 <- OR2019 %>% 
  mutate(Length = round(Length)) %>% #round length
  group_by(Ground,sex,Length) %>%  
  dplyr::mutate(total_L = n()) %>% # calculating total number of fish in each length category (by Ground and sex)
  group_by(Ground,sex) %>%  
  dplyr::mutate(total_gs = n())  # calculating the total number of fish for each group (by Ground and sex)
  
  
OR2019_prop <- OR2019 %>% 
  group_by(Ground, sex,Length) %>% 
  dplyr:: summarise(prop = n()/first(total_gs)) # summarise data for prop of total fish in each length categrory (by Gound and sex)

OR2019mean <- OR2019 %>% 
  group_by(Ground,sex) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(mean = mean(Length))

  ggplot(OR2019_prop,aes(x=Length, y= prop, colour = sex))+ # create the LF plot 
    geom_line(size = 1)+
    geom_smooth()+
    ylab("proportion of fish")+
    xlab("Length (cm)") +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(28,44,2),limits = c(28,44)) +
    #scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0,0.25,.05), limits = c(0,0.25))+
    geom_vline(data=OR2019mean, aes(xintercept=mean,  colour=sex),
             linetype="dashed", size=.5)+
    facet_wrap(~Ground)+

Figure2.3 Cummulative frequency

OR2019 <- OR2019 %>% 
  mutate(GbyS= paste(Ground,sex,sep = "_")) %>%  #new variable to combine Ground and sex 
  group_by(GbyS) %>% 
  mutate(sumsum = cumsum(Length))


#using stat_ecdf to calculate the cummulative frequency

ggplot(OR2019,aes(x=Length, colour= sex)) +
   stat_ecdf(geom = "smooth")+
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(28,44,2),limits = c(28,44))+
  facet_wrap(~Ground)+
  ylab("cummulative frequency")+
  xlab("Length (cm)")+
  theme_bw()+
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")

### Table 2 4 summarise all data by counts and mode

Number of fish measured and mode for standard lengths for males and females measured at St Helens and St Patricks from 1987 to 2013, updated from Kloser et al.2012.

#create function to find the mode
Mode <- function(x) {
    if (is.numeric(x)) {
        x_table <- table(x)
        return(as.numeric(names(x_table)[which.max(x_table)]))
    }
}


# get mode of Length for data by year, Ground and sex  
Dataformode<- Roughy1 %>% 
  mutate(GbyS= paste(Ground,sex,sep = "_")) %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(year, GbyS) %>% #group
  dplyr::summarise(mode = Mode(x= Length), n= n())  # apply Mode function

library(data.table) ## v >= 1.9.6
Table_mode <- dcast(setDT(Dataformode), year ~ GbyS, value.var = c("n", "mode"))
